import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import matplotlib.ticker as ticker
def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    plt.figure(figsize=(6, 6))
    plt.scatter(data['lon'], data['lat'])
    plt.title('What is the distribution of longitude and latitude across all capital cities?', wrap=True)
    plt.xlabel('Longitude')
    plt.ylabel('Latitude')
    plt.xticks(rotation=45)
    if len(plt.xticks()[0]) > 20:
        plt.xticks(ticker.MaxNLocator(20))
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)

import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import matplotlib.ticker as ticker

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data = data.groupby('state').count().sort_values(by='city', ascending=False)
    plt.figure(figsize=(6, 6))
    ax = plt.subplot(111)
    ax.bar(data.index, data['city'])
    plt.xticks(rotation=90)
    if len(plt.xticks()[0]) > 20:
        ax.xaxis.set_major_locator(ticker.MaxNLocator(20))
    plt.title('Which state has the highest number of capital cities?', wrap=True)
    return plt

chart = plot(data)

import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import matplotlib.ticker as ticker
def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    plt.figure(figsize=(6, 6))
    plt.scatter(data['lon'], data['lat'])
    plt.axvline(data['lon'].mean(), color='red', label=f"Mean longitude: {data['lon'].mean():.2f}")
    plt.axhline(data['lat'].mean(), color='green', label=f"Mean latitude: {data['lat'].mean():.2f}")
    plt.legend()
    plt.title("What is the average longitude and latitude of all capital cities?", wrap=True)
    if len(plt.xticks()[0]) > 20:
        plt.xticks(ticker.MaxNLocator(20))
    plt.xticks(rotation=90)
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)

import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import matplotlib.ticker as ticker
def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    plt.figure(figsize=(6, 6))
    data = data.groupby('state')
    for name, group in data:
        plt.scatter(group['lon'], group['lat'], label=name)
    plt.title('What is the distribution of longitude and latitude within each state?', wrap=True)
    plt.xlabel('Longitude')
    plt.ylabel('Latitude')
    plt.legend()
    if len(plt.xticks()[0]) > 20:
        plt.xticks(rotation=45)
        plt.gca().xaxis.set_major_locator(ticker.MaxNLocator(20))
    else:
        plt.xticks(rotation=45)
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)
